Package com.cyc.session.internal

Internal implementation classes for common Session API functionality.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractConfigurationLoader
    Abstract implementation of SessionConfigurationLoader.
    AbstractSessionConfigurationProperties
    Abstract Properties-based implementation of CycSessionConfiguration.
    ConfigurationCache
    A cache for CycSessionConfigurations.
    ConfigurationLoaderManager
    The ConfigurationLoaderManager is responsible for loading SessionConfigurationLoader services, and calling them to load configurations.
    ConfigurationValidator
    The ConfigurationValidator provides a set of simple checks to determine whether a CycSessionConfiguration object is well-formed.
    CycServerPanel
    A GUI panel which prompts the user for a Cyc hostname & base port.
    CycSessionCache<T extends CycSession>
    A cache for CycSessions.
    EnvironmentConfigurationLoader
    A SessionConfigurationLoader devoted specifically to providing EnvironmentConfigurations from System properties.
    EnvironmentConfigurationLoader.EnvironmentConfigurationImpl
    Implementation of EnvironmentConfiguration.
    GenericServerAddress
    GenericServer is a class for describing any server.
    ImmutableConfiguration
    An immutable CycSessionConfiguration implementation.
    LegacyCycAccessManager<T extends CycClientSession> Deprecated
    This class will be removed in 1.0.0-rc2
    PropertiesConfigurationLoader
    A Properties file-based SessionConfigurationLoader loader.
    PropertiesReader
    A simple utilities class that provides a few basic ways to read properties.
    SessionManagerImpl<T extends CycSession>
    Reference implementation of SessionManager.
    SimpleInteractiveLoader
    An interactive SessionConfigurationLoader which prompts the user for a CycServer address with the CycServerPanel.
    TestEnvironmentProperties
    Retrieves various test-scope configuration settings from the System properties.

Package com.cyc.session.internal Description

Internal implementation classes for common Session API functionality. Server providers implementing the Session API may wish to extends some of them, but they should otherwise be ignored.
